COMMIT_MSG_READY
item: item-36-gate-persist
date: 2026-06-14
message: |
  feat(flow-server/gate-persist): persist gate state across restarts and surface in list_items

  Gate state was in-memory only — restarting the server reset every
  WAIT/GO toggle to Go, breaking the human governance gate guarantee.

  Changes:
  - store.rs: add `gates_path` to Inner; `persist_gates()` writes an
    atomic tmp→rename JSON sidecar on every `set_gate()` call (warn-
    and-continue on sidecar fault, JSONL remains authoritative);
    `restore_gates()` reads `.flow/gates.json` on startup (missing →
    silent, corrupt → warn+go, stale IDs → silently discarded)
  - main.rs: call `store.restore_gates().await` after `ingest_roadmap()`
    so gate values survive the `upsert_item` reset (sequencing invariant)
  - mcp.rs: restructure `list_items` response from flat `{"items":[…]}`
    to `{"pending":{"wait":[…],"go":[…]},"in_progress":[…],"done":[…]}`

  Test evidence:
  - 11 new unit/contract tests in store_contract_intest.rs covering all
    branches: atomic write, toggle, restart restore, missing/corrupt/
    empty file resilience, stale-ID discard, sequencing invariant,
    sidecar fault warn-continue
  - 3 new + 1 updated MCP contract tests covering grouped list_items shape
  - 5 story tests (STORY-G36-01 through -05) exercising simulated restart,
    corrupt cold-start, grouping, and real-time toggle
  - All 309 Rust tests pass; 299 JS vitest tests pass

  Closes [36]

  EARS: EARS-G36-01 through EARS-G36-08
  Sentinel: STORY_PROVEN
